This transcript reproduces the failure modes of the four existing observer
pages (`/features/observers`, `/building/observers`, `/building/observer-
webhook-patterns`, `/operations/observer-runbook`) against the v2.3.2
binary by feeding the binary a TOML config that mirrors the page-documented
shape verbatim, then observing what the binary actually does.

## Overlay applied (mirrors features/observers.mdx L24-L29 + building/observers.mdx L50-L67)

bind_addr = "0.0.0.0:8080"
database_url = "postgresql://fraiseql:fraiseql_docs_test@postgres:5432/fraiseql"
schema_path = "/etc/fraiseql/schema.compiled.json"
cors_enabled = true
cors_origins = ["http://localhost:8080"]
health_path = "/health"
playground_enabled = false
metrics_enabled = false
admin_api_enabled = false
introspection_enabled = false
pool_min_size = 5
pool_max_size = 20
pool_timeout_secs = 30

# === verbatim from features/observers.mdx + building/observers.mdx ===
[observers]
enabled   = true
backend   = "redis"
redis_url = "redis://redis:6379"
nats_url  = "nats://nats:4222"

[[observers.handlers]]
name        = "welcome-email"
event       = "user.created"
action      = "webhook"
webhook_url = "http://example.invalid/welcome"
retry_strategy = "exponential"
max_retries    = 3

## Observation 1 ŌĆö server BOOTED HEALTHY despite `backend`/`redis_url`/`nats_url`/`[[handlers]]`
##                  being silent-swallow keys against ServerConfig.

`./docs-test.sh up --profile fraiseql` returned exit 0. Container went
Healthy. Log shows ONE attempt at `Initializing observer runtime` ŌĆö
no parse error, no "unknown field 'backend'", no "unknown field 'handlers'":

  fraiseql-1 | 2026-05-29T22:21:52.527452Z  INFO  Initializing observer PostgreSQL pool min=2 max=5 timeout_secs=10
  fraiseql-1 | 2026-05-29T22:21:52.550105Z  INFO  Initializing observer runtime
  fraiseql-1 | 2026-05-29T22:21:52.551691Z  INFO  Observer runtime attached to AppState for health probes
  fraiseql-1 | 2026-05-29T22:21:52.562926Z  INFO  Observer management, runtime health, and DLQ delivery status endpoints enabled path="/api/observers"
  fraiseql-1 | 2026-05-29T22:21:52.565495Z  INFO  Starting observer runtime...
  fraiseql-1 | 2026-05-29T22:21:52.566269Z  INFO  Starting observer runtime...
  fraiseql-1 | 2026-05-29T22:21:52.568221Z ERROR  Failed to start observer runtime: Database error: error returned from database: relation "tb_observer" does not exist
  fraiseql-1 | 2026-05-29T22:21:52.568443Z  WARN  Server will continue without observers

The binary's `ServerConfig` parser silently ignores `backend`, `redis_url`,
`nats_url`, and the `[[observers.handlers]]` array-of-tables ŌĆö none of those
keys exist on `ObserverConfig` (`crates/fraiseql-server/src/server_config/
observers.rs:L99-L130`). `ServerConfig` carries no `#[serde(deny_unknown_
fields)]` attribute (`server_config/mod.rs:L40-L42`), so unknown TOML keys
are dropped on the floor with no diagnostic. This is the same
silent-swallow class as FW-7 (`/features/file-storage` Cycle 2 RED).

## Observation 2 ŌĆö observer DEFINITIONS are loaded from the DATABASE, not TOML.

The frozen-SHA binary's observer runtime calls
`self.repository.list(...)` against `tb_observer` at startup
(`crates/fraiseql-server/src/observers/runtime.rs:L189-L221`). The Cycle-2
docs-test PostgreSQL fixture has no `tb_observer` table, so the boot path
errors `relation "tb_observer" does not exist`. The
`[[observers.handlers]]` array-of-tables documented in all four current
pages is NOT the runtime configuration surface ŌĆö it does not produce a
single registered observer. Observers must be installed in
`tb_observer` (the schema is at
`crates/fraiseql-observers/migrations/06_create_observer_management.sql`
in the framework tree, not bundled with the binary or auto-applied).

## Observation 3 ŌĆö `[[observers.handlers]]` shape ONLY exists in fraiseql-cli's
##                  config-validation schema, not in fraiseql-server's runtime config.

  $ git -C ~/code/fraiseql show d0a4ed4ec:crates/fraiseql-cli/src/config/toml_schema/observers.rs

  pub struct ObserversConfig {
      pub enabled:   bool,
      pub backend:   String,
      pub redis_url: Option<String>,
      pub nats_url:  Option<String>,
      pub handlers:  Vec<EventHandler>,    // <-- matches docs
  }
  pub struct EventHandler {
      pub name:           String,
      pub event:          String,
      pub action:         String,
      pub webhook_url:    Option<String>,
      pub retry_strategy: Option<String>,
      pub max_retries:    Option<u32>,
      pub description:    Option<String>,
  }

  $ git -C ~/code/fraiseql show d0a4ed4ec:crates/fraiseql-server/src/server_config/observers.rs

  pub struct ObserverConfig {
      pub enabled: bool,
      pub poll_interval_ms: u64,
      pub batch_size: usize,
      pub channel_capacity: usize,
      pub auto_reload: bool,
      pub reload_interval_secs: u64,
      pub pool: ObserverPoolConfig,
  }

`fraiseql-cli`'s `ObserversConfig` is a *validation type* used by
`fraiseql-cli compile`'s TOML-schema validator. `fraiseql-server` reads its
own `ObserverConfig` shape at startup and consumes a completely different
set of fields. The two structures share neither `backend` nor `handlers`.

## Observation 4 ŌĆö route mounting is inconsistent.

  $ curl http://localhost:8080/api/observers
  HTTP/1.1 500
  {"error":"Database error: error returned from database: relation \"tb_observer\" does not exist"}

  $ curl http://localhost:8080/api/observers/dlq
  HTTP/1.1 200
  {"items":[],"total":0,"limit":50,"offset":0}

  $ curl http://localhost:8080/api/observers/runtime/health
  HTTP/1.1 404

  $ curl http://localhost:8080/runtime/health     ŌåÉ actual route
  HTTP/1.1 503
  {"errors":0,"events_processed":0,"last_checkpoint":0,"observer_count":0,"running":false}

`observer_runtime_routes` is `app.merge(...)` at the router ROOT, not nested
under `/api/observers` like the other observer routers
(`crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/routing/observers.rs:L46-L62`). The
runbook page's status-endpoint advice ŌĆö referencing `fraiseql_observer_*`
metric labels and the runtime CLI commands ŌĆö does not match this layout.

## Observation 5 ŌĆö `/health` reports `status: degraded`, NOT `healthy`,
##                  when the observer subsystem failed to start.

  $ curl http://localhost:8080/health
  {"status":"degraded",
   "database":{"connected":true,"database_type":"PostgreSQL",...},
   "observers":{"running":false,"pending_events":0},
   "version":"2.3.2","schema_hash":"316c9100f7a872c8c411033ac2a00066"}

The four pages do not document this degraded-state contract or the
`tb_observer` schema-bootstrap requirement.

## Observation 6 ŌĆö `fraiseql-cli observer dlq list` etc. (referenced
##                  throughout /operations/observer-runbook) DO NOT EXIST.

`fraiseql-cli`'s `Cargo.toml` (`crates/fraiseql-cli/Cargo.toml`) does NOT
depend on `fraiseql-observers`; the CLI binary has no `observer`
subcommand at all. The CLI surface lives in `fraiseql-observers/src/cli/`
behind the `cli` feature gate, exposed as a separate
`fraiseql-observers` binary (CLI app name in `clap`:
`#[command(name = "fraiseql-observers")]`).

Even where the CLI exists, the `dlq list` / `show` / `stats` / `retry`
handlers in `crates/fraiseql-observers/src/cli/commands/dlq.rs:L38-L80`
return HARD-CODED MOCK JSON, not real DLQ contents ŌĆö observer IDs
`obs-webhook`/`obs-email`/`obs-slack` are baked into the source. The
runbook's CLI workflows are inoperable on the frozen SHA.

## Observation 7 ŌĆö `[observers.pool]` IS a real field.

The runbook is partially correct: `ObserverPoolConfig` does exist
(`crates/fraiseql-server/src/server_config/observers.rs:L51-L65`,
defaults at L68-L80). The frozen-SHA boot log confirms:

  fraiseql-1 | INFO Initializing observer PostgreSQL pool min=2 max=5 timeout_secs=10

So `[observers.pool] min_connections / max_connections / acquire_timeout_secs`
are valid. The four pages either don't document this section or document it
adjacent to invalid TOML.

## Observation 8 ŌĆö backend list in CHANGELOG / Cargo.toml says
##                  postgres / nats / in_memory, NOT redis / postgresql / mysql / in-memory.

The pages list five "backends": `in-memory`, `nats`, `redis`,
`postgres`/`postgresql`, `mysql`. The framework's `TransportKind` enum
(`crates/fraiseql-observers/src/config/transport.rs:L15-L42`) has THREE
variants: `Postgres` (default), `Nats`, `InMemory`. Redis is a CACHE /
JOB-QUEUE / DEDUP / LEASE backend, not an event-transport backend
(`crates/fraiseql-observers/Cargo.toml:L52-L68`). MySQL appears only as
a *bridge* (MySQL ŌåÆ NATS), not as a standalone event transport
(`crates/fraiseql-observers/src/transport/mysql_bridge.rs:L1-L31`).

## Summary of contradictions per page

- `/features/observers.mdx`
  - L24-L29 `[observers] backend = "redis"` block: silently ignored (Obs. 1).
  - L40 "at-least-once delivery": confirmable (`retry.rs:L17-L80`).
  - L44 "distributed lease" claim: real but feature-gated
    (`redis-lease` not enabled in default CARGO_FEATURES; lease is
    `in_process` unless `postgres`/`redis-lease` is wired ŌĆö
    `crates/fraiseql-observers/src/listener/lease.rs:L1-L18`).
  - L62-L65 "FraiseQL server registers listeners at startup and routes
    each event to matching observers": the binary does this only if
    `tb_observer` exists (Obs. 2) ŌĆö undocumented.

- `/building/observers.mdx`
  - L50-L67 `[observers]` + `[[observers.handlers]]`: silently ignored
    (Obs. 1, Obs. 3).
  - L40-L43 architecture diagram showing TOML ŌåÆ handlers: factually
    wrong (Obs. 2).

- `/building/observer-webhook-patterns.mdx`
  - L36-L60 `[observers] backend = "nats"|"redis"|"postgres"`:
    silently ignored (Obs. 1) ŌĆö only Postgres-NOTIFY is the live transport
    on the frozen SHA without the `observers-nats` feature; with it
    `TransportConfig::transport` may be set, but NOT through the documented
    `[observers] backend = ...` key.
  - L68-L78 event-payload shape `fraiseql.order.created`: cannot be
    verified against the binary without an installed `tb_observer` row
    (Obs. 2).

- `/operations/observer-runbook.mdx`
  - L41-L62 alert rules: metric names appear in
    `crates/fraiseql-observers/src/metrics/registry.rs` (need to spot-check;
    most likely real).
  - L67-L71 `fraiseql-cli observer status`: does not exist (Obs. 6).
  - L120-L171 `fraiseql-cli observer dlq list|show|retry|remove`: do not
    exist; if you build the `fraiseql-observers` CLI binary separately, the
    handlers return hard-coded mock JSON (Obs. 6).
  - L94-L100 `max_dlq_size` callout: real field on `ObserverRuntimeConfig`
    (`crates/fraiseql-observers/src/config/runtime.rs:L55-L67`) ŌĆö but on
    the *library-API* runtime config, NOT on the binary's `[observers]`
    section. Same library-vs-binary gap as Cycle 1 / Cycle 2.

## What the GREEN Writer must do

1. Replace `[[observers.handlers]]` array-of-tables prose with the binary's
   actual `[observers]` schema: `enabled`, `poll_interval_ms`, `batch_size`,
   `channel_capacity`, `auto_reload`, `reload_interval_secs`,
   `[observers.pool]` (sub-table).
2. Document the DB-driven observer model: observers live in `tb_observer`,
   not TOML. The migration is at
   `crates/fraiseql-observers/migrations/06_create_observer_management.sql`
   and is NOT auto-applied by the binary.
3. Document the `POST /api/observers` HTTP API for creating observers
   (route mounting: `crates/fraiseql-server/src/observers/routes.rs:L34-L51`).
4. Document the route-mount inconsistency: `/runtime/health` (root) vs.
   `/api/observers/*` ŌĆö and file FW-13 (this) if not already filed.
5. Document that `fraiseql-cli` has no observer commands. The
   `fraiseql-observers` CLI binary returns mocked data ŌĆö runbook usage
   patterns need a rewrite or a `## Known issues` block.
6. Use the **library-API framing (option A)** consistent with Cycle 1 /
   Cycle 2 GREEN: the binary auto-wires observer routes, but the
   user-facing TOML config the docs advertise (`backend`/`handlers`)
   is the `fraiseql-cli compile`-time validation schema, NOT the runtime
   schema ŌĆö they share a name but not a contract.

